* Videos

You can put a video by writing "@video [/URL/]", where the URL refers to an arbitrary external image resource.  The browser renders a control panel to operate the video content.  Layout rules are the same as those of images.

@video https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap1]
@video https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap1] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap2]
@video https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap1] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap2] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap3]
@video https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap1] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap2] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap3] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap4]
@video https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap1] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap2] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap3] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap4] | https://dbmx.net/misc/design-a.mov [caption=cap5]

* Youtube

You can embed a youtube video by writing "@youtube [/URL/]", where the URL is the content link with "?v=[/xxxxxxxx/]" parameter.  Specifying only the "[/xxxxxxxx/]" is also enough.

@youtube https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hln6MoTKnUc [caption=cap1]
@youtube Hln6MoTKnUc [caption=cap1] | Hln6MoTKnUc [caption=cap2]
